| :--- | :--- |
| **`isdigit(c)`** | Is it a number `0-9`? |
| **`isalpha(c)`** | Is it a letter `a-z` or `A-Z`? |
| **`isalnum(c)`** | Is it a letter OR a number? |
| **`isspace(c)`** | Is it a space, tab, or newline? |
| **`ispunct(c)`** | Is it puncuation like `!`, `-`, or `.`? |
| **`isupper(c)`** | Is it an UPPERCASE letter? |


## Formatting (`<iomanip>`)
**Required Includes:** `#include <iomanip>` and `#include <iostream>` (or `<fstream>`)

| Manipulator | Purpose | Example / Output |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **`std::fixed`** | Forces decimal notation (prevents scientific notation). *(Sticky)* | `cout << fixed << 1000.0;` // *1000.000000* |
| **`std::setprecision(n)`** | Sets the exact number of digits after the decimal point. *(Sticky)* | `cout << setprecision(2) << 3.14159;` // *3.14* |
| **`std::setw(n)`** | Creates a box of `n` spaces for the **very next** item. *(Not Sticky)* | `cout << "[" << setw(5) << 42 << "]";` // *[   42]* |
| **`std::left`** | Pushes the text to the left side of the `setw` box. *(Sticky)* | `cout << left << setw(5) << 42;` // *42   * |
| **`std::right`** | Pushes the text to the right side of the `setw` box. *(Sticky)* | `cout << right << setw(5) << 42;` // * 42* |
| **`std::setfill(char)`** | Changes the padding character used by `setw`. *(Sticky)* | `cout << setfill('0') << setw(4) << 5;` // *0005* |


## HOW TO READ A CSV FILE
```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <fstream>
#include <sstream>
#include <vector>
#include <string>

// Define a struct to hold a row of data, e.g., for data.csv: Name,Age,Occupation
struct Person {
    std::string name;
    int age;
    std::string occupation;
};

int main() {
    std::ifstream file("data.csv"); // Open the CSV file
    std::string line;
    std::vector<Person> data; // Vector to store Person structs

    // Check if the file opened successfully
    if (!file.is_open()) {
        std::cerr << "Error opening file!" << std::endl;
        return 1;
    }

    // Skip the header line (optional, depending on your file)
    std::getline(file, line);

    // Read the file line by line
    while (std::getline(file, line)) {
        std::istringstream iss(line); // Create a string stream from the line
        std::string word;
        Person person;

        // Extract data fields using the comma delimiter
        std::getline(iss, person.name, ','); // Read name until the first comma
        std::getline(iss, word, ',');       // Read age as a string
        person.age = std::stoi(word);       // Convert age string to integer
        std::getline(iss, person.occupation); // Read the rest of the line (occupation)

        data.push_back(person); // Add the person struct to the vector
    }
    file.close(); // Close the file

    // Display the parsed data
    for (const auto& person : data) {
        std::cout << "Name: " << person.name << ", Age: " << person.age
                  << ", Occupation: " << person.occupation << std::endl;
    }

    return 0;
}
```


## HEADER
```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <stdio.h>

using namespace std;

int main() {
    char exitInput;

    do {
        system("CLS");
        
        int menuNumber;
        while (true) {
            printf("Menu 1\nMenu 2\nMenu 3\nMenu 4\nWhat menu do you want? \n");
            if (cin >> menuNumber && menuNumber >= 0) {
                break;
            }

            cin.clear();
            cin.ignore(1000, '\n');
        }

        switch (menuNumber) {
            case 1:
                printf("oh cool menu 1\n");
                break;
            case 2:
                printf("oh cool menu 2\n");
                break;
            case 3:
                printf("oh cool menu 3\n");
                break;
            case 4:
                printf("oh cool menu 4\n");
                break;
            default:
                printf("that isnt a menu number!\n");
                break;
        }

        printf("Want to go again? (y/Y): ");
        cin >> exitInput;
    } while (exitInput == 'y' || exitInput == 'Y');

    return 0;
}
```


## FILE I/O
```cpp
std::ofstream outFile("marathonList.txt");
    
double totalAge = 0;
double totalFees = 0;
if (outFile.is_open()) {
    for (Runner runner : runners) {
       char buffer[128];
        std::snprintf(buffer, sizeof(buffer), "%d | %s | %d | %s | %.2f\n", runner.getBib(), runner.getName().c_str(), runner.getAge(), runner.getCategory().c_str(), runner.getRegistrationFee());
        outFile << buffer;

        totalAge += runner.getAge();
        totalFees += runner.getRegistrationFee();
    }

    char buffer[128];
    std::snprintf(buffer, sizeof(buffer), "\nAverage age: %.2f\nTotal fees: %.2f", totalAge / runners.size(), totalFees);
    outFile << buffer;

    outFile.close();
} else {
    std::cerr << "Error: Could not open the file." << std::endl;
}
```